<paragraph id="8BA8391AFF85F60FFF7F0B811D9AF82A" blockId="12.[151,604,1901,1961]" box="[151,249,1936,1961]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
(
<figureCitation id="132C259FFF85F60FFF770B811D92F82A" box="[159,241,1936,1961]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1870,1893]" captionTargetBox="[180,1410,208,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1410,195,1857]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. (62 – 66) Apogonalia mediolineata (Fowler, 1899), female: 62, dorsal habitus; 63, face; 64, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 65, pygofer, lateral view; 66, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (67) A. monticola (Fowler, 1899), female: 67, dorsal habitus. (68) A. noda Freytag, 2004, female: 68, dorsal habitus. (69 – 74) A. omani Young, 1977, female: 69, dorsal habitus; 70, left forewing, lateral view; 71, sternite VII, ventral view; 72, pygofer, lateral view; 73, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 74, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035598/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
