<subSubSection id="C30D6A91FF85F60EFF7F0BC91F36FD9B" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="114" pageId="12" pageNumber="113" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA8391AFF85F60EFF7F0BC91F38FE76" blockId="12.[151,1436,2008,2033]" lastBlockId="13.[151,1436,151,933]" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="114" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">
<emphasis id="B963E508FF85F60FFF7F0BC91C72F873" bold="true" box="[151,273,2008,2033]" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Anterior dorsum black with mosaic of yellow maculae. Crown (
<figureCitation id="132C259FFF85F60FFBE00BC9193EF872" box="[1032,1117,2008,2033]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1870,1893]" captionTargetBox="[180,1410,208,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1410,195,1857]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. (62 – 66) Apogonalia mediolineata (Fowler, 1899), female: 62, dorsal habitus; 63, face; 64, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 65, pygofer, lateral view; 66, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (67) A. monticola (Fowler, 1899), female: 67, dorsal habitus. (68) A. noda Freytag, 2004, female: 68, dorsal habitus. (69 – 74) A. omani Young, 1977, female: 69, dorsal habitus; 70, left forewing, lateral view; 71, sternite VII, ventral view; 72, pygofer, lateral view; 73, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 74, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035598/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="113">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
) with pair of anteromedian diagonal pale yellow arches; posterolateral margins pale yellow. Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="132C259FFF84F60EFC120C86192DFF33" box="[1018,1102,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1870,1893]" captionTargetBox="[180,1410,208,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1410,195,1857]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. (62 – 66) Apogonalia mediolineata (Fowler, 1899), female: 62, dorsal habitus; 63, face; 64, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 65, pygofer, lateral view; 66, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (67) A. monticola (Fowler, 1899), female: 67, dorsal habitus. (68) A. noda Freytag, 2004, female: 68, dorsal habitus. (69 – 74) A. omani Young, 1977, female: 69, dorsal habitus; 70, left forewing, lateral view; 71, sternite VII, ventral view; 72, pygofer, lateral view; 73, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 74, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035598/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
) posterolaterally with pair of oblique, elongate bright yellow marks. Mesonotum (
<figureCitation id="132C259FFF84F60EFCE80CAD1E36FF56" box="[768,853,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1870,1893]" captionTargetBox="[180,1410,208,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1410,195,1857]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. (62 – 66) Apogonalia mediolineata (Fowler, 1899), female: 62, dorsal habitus; 63, face; 64, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 65, pygofer, lateral view; 66, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (67) A. monticola (Fowler, 1899), female: 67, dorsal habitus. (68) A. noda Freytag, 2004, female: 68, dorsal habitus. (69 – 74) A. omani Young, 1977, female: 69, dorsal habitus; 70, left forewing, lateral view; 71, sternite VII, ventral view; 72, pygofer, lateral view; 73, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 74, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035598/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
) black with yellow maculae: one pair anterior to transverse sulcus, one elongate posteromedian pair, and one elongate lateral pair. Forewing (
<figureCitation id="132C259FFF84F60EFB5E0CCE186AFF7B" box="[1206,1289,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 62 – 74" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1870,1893]" captionTargetBox="[180,1410,208,1857]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[180,1410,195,1857]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 62 – 74. (62 – 66) Apogonalia mediolineata (Fowler, 1899), female: 62, dorsal habitus; 63, face; 64, sternite VIII, dorsal view; 65, pygofer, lateral view; 66, valvula II, teeth on median portion, lateral view. (67) A. monticola (Fowler, 1899), female: 67, dorsal habitus. (68) A. noda Freytag, 2004, female: 68, dorsal habitus. (69 – 74) A. omani Young, 1977, female: 69, dorsal habitus; 70, left forewing, lateral view; 71, sternite VII, ventral view; 72, pygofer, lateral view; 73, valvulae I, basal portion, ventral view; 74, valvula II, apical portion, lateral view. Scale bars in mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1035598/files/figure.png" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
) dark brown with white maculae on anterior third, pink maculae on posterior two-thirds; commissural margin pale yellow except basally; apex brown, hyaline. Face black with numerous small pale yellow maculae. Clypeus with lateral margin pale yellow. Male pygofer with inner ventroapical short spiniform process. Paraphyses asymmetrical, with Y-shaped basal sclerite and at least one long, moderately broad ramus (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8644EBFF84F60EFC430D6119C8FE0B" author="Young" box="[939,1195,367,392]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" refString="Young, D. A. (1977) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 2. New World Cicadellini and the genus Cicadella. Technical Bulletin of the North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station, 239, 1 - 1135." type="journal article" year="1977" yearSuffix="h">Young 1977, fig. 760h</bibRefCitation>
). Aedeagal shaft with apex curved dorsally, with pair of long ventromedian spiniform processes (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8644EBFF84F60EFC370D8519BEFE2E" author="Young" box="[991,1245,404,429]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" refString="Young, D. A. (1977) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 2. New World Cicadellini and the genus Cicadella. Technical Bulletin of the North Carolina Agricultural Experiment Station, 239, 1 - 1135." type="journal article" year="1977" yearSuffix="f">Young 1977, fig. 760f</bibRefCitation>
). Female sternite VIII with semilunar sclerotized plate, anteriorly with pair of slight concavities. Female pygofer broadly convex ventrally. Valvula II with apex subacute.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BA8391AFF84F60EFF2F0DEE1F36FD9B" blockId="13.[151,1436,151,933]" box="[199,597,511,536]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">
Female length. 
<quantity id="4CEF94FFFF84F60EFE9C0DEE1C98FD94" box="[372,507,511,536]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="9.6" metricValueMin="9.4" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" unit="mm" value="9.5" valueMax="9.6" valueMin="9.4">9.4–9.6 mm</quantity>
(n = 2).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30D6A91FF84F60EFF2F0E351FD4FC03" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BA8391AFF84F60EFF2F0E351FD4FC03" blockId="13.[151,1436,151,933]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis id="B963E508FF84F60EFF2F0E351F5AFDB8" bold="true" box="[199,569,548,573]" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">Description of female genitalia.</emphasis>
Sternite VII similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C174299FF84F60EFC600E351E9CFDBF" authorityName="Freytag" authorityYear="2004" box="[904,1023,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="angusta">
<emphasis id="B963E508FF84F60EFC600E351E9CFDBF" box="[904,1023,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">A. angusta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; posterior margin with slight median concavity. Sternite VIII, in dorsal view, with semilunar sclerotized plate; anterior margin with pair of lateral slight concavities. Pygofer moderately produced posteriorly; posterior margin broadly convex; disc with some macrosetae on posterior two-thirds of ventral portion and apical portion. Valvula I, in ventral view, with basal portion moderately broad; basal margin truncate; blade similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="4C174299FF84F60EFC050EA5193AFD4F" baseAuthorityName="Fabricius" baseAuthorityYear="1794" box="[1005,1113,692,716]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Apogonalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="114" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="histrio">
<emphasis id="B963E508FF84F60EFC050EA5193AFD4F" box="[1005,1113,692,716]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="114">A. histrio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Valvula II, in lateral view, moderately broad beyond basal curvature, slightly narrowing towards subacute apex; blade with about 25 teeth distributed from beginning of expanded portion to apex; teeth, on median portion, triangular and moderately prominent, about 1.5 times longer than high, spaced from one another about one tooth length; preapical prominence distinct, approximately aligned to anteapical tooth; denticles distributed on all dorsal margin of blade and from preapical prominence to apex on ventral margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
